{"key":"post-7296695","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>7296695</id>\n<content>Keep it simple.  Three to five inches of well drained perlite will deliver 99% humidity in a terrarium. You don't need humidifiers, bubblers, positive pressure, etc. You can fan several times daily or drill a bunch of holes in the sides, top and bottom of the terrarium and cut back on fanning.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>7296965</next>\n<prev>7296292</prev>\n<first>7296017</first>\n<last>7297125</last>\n<when>1187182819</when>\n<utime>08/15/07 04:00 PM</utime>\n</post>"}